B is the second letter of the Latin alphabet.

wiki.text:
'B' (named bee <ref>"B" Oxford English Dictionary, 2nd edition (1989); Merriam-
Webster's Third New International Dictionary of the English Language, Unabridged
(1993); "bee", op. cit.</ref>) is the second letter in the ISO basic Latin
alphabet. It is used to represent a variety of bilabial sounds (depending on
language), but most commonly a voiced bilabial stop.
